The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Helicopter catches fire
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Helicopter catches fire
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Chandigarh Dec. 16: Two pilots were injured today when a Punjab government helicopter that was to ferry a state minister burst into flames minutes before take-off.         
	The Dauphin N3 chopper had been leased from Pawan Hans and was on its way to a helipad near chief minister Parkash Singh Badals residence where minister Manoranjan Kalia was to board it to fly to Hoshiarpur.        
	Kalia was waiting at the helipad when the chopper tilted and burst into flames. The helicopter was taxiing for takeoff when it tilted. The two pilots, S.P.S. Brar and M.S. Brar, suffered some injuries, a government spokesperson said. The directorate-general of civil aviation has ordered an inquiry.                                                                                                                                                           
